		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.68]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Jiggidyjay&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>My main is a 67 VS bard. I love my bard.<br><br><blockquote><b id="fs8">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />monks being gimped, necros only soloing, rangers dying in 5 seconds, zerkers pretty much sucking<hr size="1" /></blockquote><br><br>None of that is really true (except the zerker part, to a point). Monks aren't gimp. Necros are welcomed more and more into groups. Rangers don't die nearly as often as they did back in the Kunark days, especially if they're played well, bards can still solo regardless of the big AE nerf... A lot of those flames were fueled by anger over &quot;nerfs&quot;. The thing is, the game changes, all the time, and always will. That's one of the things that keeps people coming back. Class balancing is an extremely difficult thing to try and accomplish, and the truth of the matter is, they will never be completely balanced, without making some very fundamental changes to the gameplay, most of which I don't think anybody really wants.<br><br>That being said, SOE has just released <i>some</i> of their plans for class reinvisionment. Just about everybody is angry over their classes reinvisionments, and jealous over the other classes. I was looking at monkly business today, and they're COMPLAINING that the mitigation unnerf isn't good enough. It's the first thing SOE plans on doing, and it's not good enough... give me a break. People aren't happy unless they're complaining, and that's where a lot of these class stereotypes come from.<br><br>Anyway, as for the server populations... /pushes default reply: Morden Rasp, Maelyn Starpyre and a couple of others have decent low level populations from what I hear. Most servers are mostly higher end, and if you go with them starting new, you'll either be soloing a lot or playing with mostly twinked out alts. SOE has already done some server merges in response to the other next gen MMOs that came out; combining all of the PvP servers into one and combining 2 high population servers with 2 low population servers (to make 2 &quot;more-then-highly populated servers). They plan on doing this more if the need arises. It's still going pretty strong though. It's not as crowded as back in the PoP hay-days, but there doesn't seem to be too many problems getting groups on my server at least.<br><br><i><span class="sm">Edited, Mon Mar 21 23:55:49 2005 by Jiggidyjay</span class="sm"></i></p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br /><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1006062" target="akztarg">Jiggidyjay</a> - <span class="sm">Mr Ranger</span class="sm"><br><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1003866" target="akztarg">Zingin Ansinging</a> - <span class="sm">Mr Bard of <a href="HTTP://firestormers.com/viewnews.php" target="akztarg">The Firestormers</a></span class="sm"><br><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1006061" target="akztarg">Zolotaya</a> - <span class="sm">Ms Necro</span class="sm"><br><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1189723" target="akztarg">Zeibis</a> - <span class="sm">Mr Monk</span class="sm"></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from the Oval Office.</td></tr></table>
