		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.52]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Jiggidyjay&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>LadyP, sometimes you seem bi-polar. One day you'll seem like a cool person, then the next you'll flame like someone pi**ed in your Cheerios. Maybe you're just having a bad day. Regardless...<br><br>LadyP is right about one thing. Bards aren't meant to be tanks. I don't think anybody said anything about tanking with a bard... but yeah. You'll basically want to look for the same stats any melee class would look for; HP/AC/some Dex (not in that particular order, depends on your playstyle) and you'll want CHA. There are differing arguments about how much CHA is enough... I personally like CHA a lot, hence my 275 or so unbuffed CHA (check Zingin's magelo in my sig, which still hasn't been resynched since like a month ago).<br><br><blockquote><b id="fs8">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />Zerks dont suck, who told you that?<hr size="1" /></blockquote><br><br>I've personally only met 2. And my guild only has 1, and it's an alt (I think, never actually seen them logged on), yet we don't recruit for them. That tells me that either there's something fundamentally wrong with them, or they just don't contribute anything unique enough to be sought after. True, that doesn't mean they suck, but I think they're more of a &quot;good concept, bad implementation&quot; deal then anything.<br><br><blockquote><b id="fs8">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />and sick and tired of the rangers jokes<hr size="1" /></blockquote><br><br>Doesn't matter, they won't stop. It may not be so true now-a-days, but it's part of EQ culture. As Elinda said, most of the people I know that make ranger jokes the most are in fact themselves rangers...<br><br><blockquote><b id="fs8">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />and bards are weak and are not tanks and will die just as fast as any class, if not more, bards are only as good as they play/sing a song..<hr size="1" /></blockquote><br><br>As I pointed out, you're correct, bards are not tanks. We don't put out massive DPS either (slightly less then BL's probably, minus the pet, which by itself is pretty weak). What we bring to the table is the ability to improve the entire group with some pretty unique focii/abilities/songs. Being a good bard has nothing to do with how &quot;good&quot; you play/sing a song. Anybody can twist. It's about knowing your abilities and songs and being able to determine when to bring that 1 song you've only used twice out of the song book, because it'll be perfect for the current situation and knowing which songs to play to give the group the most benefit possible. No song lineup will be ideal for every situation or group.</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br /><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1006062" target="akztarg">Jiggidyjay</a> - <span class="sm">Mr Ranger</span class="sm"><br><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1003866" target="akztarg">Zingin Ansinging</a> - <span class="sm">Mr Bard of <a href="HTTP://firestormers.com/viewnews.php" target="akztarg">The Firestormers</a></span class="sm"><br><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1006061" target="akztarg">Zolotaya</a> - <span class="sm">Ms Necro</span class="sm"><br><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1189723" target="akztarg">Zeibis</a> - <span class="sm">Mr Monk</span class="sm"></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from the Oval Office.</td></tr></table>
